Butula Technical & Vocational College	Butula Technical & Vocational College is a public TVET institution located in Butula town, Busia County. It offers quality technical and vocational training programs approved by KUCCPS, equipping students with essential skills for employment and entrepreneurship in various technical fields.	COLLEGE	BUTULA TVC	Busia County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/5150/	PUBLIC	Butula Technical & Vocational College (Butula TVC) is a public tertiary institution situated in Butula town, Butula Constituency, within Busia County, Kenya. Operating under the Ministry of Education, the college is mandated to provide accessible and quality technical and vocational education and training (TVET) programs. Established to serve the training needs of the western region of Kenya, Butula TVC plays a crucial role in developing a skilled workforce capable of contributing to national development and meeting the demands of various industries. Its location makes it a key educational hub for students from Busia and neighboring counties seeking practical, hands-on training.\n\nThe college offers a diverse range of programs across various disciplines, including engineering technology, business studies, information and communication technology (ICT), hospitality, and agriculture, among others. These courses are structured to provide students with both theoretical knowledge and practical skills, enhancing their employability and entrepreneurial potential. Butula TVC is equipped with workshops, laboratories, and learning resources necessary to facilitate effective technical training. By focusing on demand-driven courses and maintaining close links with industry, Butula TVC has built a reputation as a reliable provider of market-ready graduates, significantly contributing to the socio-economic empowerment of the youth in the region.	Ministry of Education	["TVC", "College", "Technical", "Vocational"]	01986e2b-d056-7632-8d49-1f95f2675537	2025-10-06 14:51:29.591543	2025-08-03 04:23:41.910723	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	butula-technical-vocational-college
David M Wambuli Technical Vocational College	David M Wambuli Technical Vocational College (DMWTVC) is a public TVET institution in Wote, Makueni County, offering diverse technical and vocational programs to equip students with practical skills for employment and entrepreneurship opportunities.	COLLEGE	DAVID M WAMBULI TVC	Makueni County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/3720/	PUBLIC	David M Wambuli Technical Vocational College (DMWTVC) is a public technical and vocational education and training institution located in Wote Town, Makueni County, Kenya. The college is strategically positioned in the county headquarters, serving the educational needs of students from Makueni and neighbouring counties. Established as part of the government's initiative to enhance TVET training across the country, DMWTVC is registered and regulated by the Technical and Vocational Education and Training Authority (TVETA). It plays a crucial role in providing market-relevant skills and knowledge to empower the youth for employment and entrepreneurship, contributing significantly to the socio-economic development of the region.\n\nDMWTVC offers a diverse range of technical, vocational, and business-related courses at certificate and diploma levels. The college boasts qualified trainers and facilities aimed at providing hands-on practical training alongside theoretical knowledge. The programs cover various fields, including engineering, building technology, business studies, information communication technology, and more. As a KUCCPS-accredited institution, it attracts students placed by the central body as well as self-sponsored students. The institution is committed to producing competent and skilled graduates who can meet the demands of the evolving job market and drive innovation within their respective industries.	Ministry of Education	["TVC", "College", "Technical", "Vocational"]	01986e2c-8073-7df7-acea-4deefbc8ad6c	2025-10-06 14:51:29.591561	2025-08-03 04:24:26.996231	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	david-m-wambuli-technical-vocational-college
Fayya Technical And Vocational College	Fayya Technical And Vocational College is a public TVET institution situated in Bura, Tana River County. It offers a wide array of practical technical, vocational, and business programs aimed at empowering students with skills for employment and entrepreneurship.	COLLEGE	FAYYA TVC	Tana River County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/4570/	PUBLIC	Fayya Technical And Vocational College is a public institution located in Bura, Tana River County, Kenya. Established under the Ministry of Education, the college is dedicated to providing relevant and market-driven technical and vocational education and training (TVET) to young Kenyans. It plays a crucial role in enhancing access to post-secondary education and skill development opportunities in the Tana River region, which is essential for socio-economic growth and poverty reduction. The college is registered and regulated by the Technical and Vocational Education and Training Authority (TVETA) and participates in the Kenya Universities and Colleges Central Placement Service (KUCCPS) system, admitting students from across the country for various diploma, certificate, and artisan courses.\n\nThe college offers a diverse range of programs spanning multiple disciplines designed to meet the current demands of industry and the economy. Key areas of study often include various engineering trades (such as Building Technology, Electrical and Electronic Engineering), business studies, information communication technology (ICT), agriculture, fashion design, hospitality, and other technical courses like plumbing and welding. By focusing on practical training and hands-on skills, Fayya TVC aims to equip its graduates with the competencies needed for direct employment or entrepreneurship, contributing to the workforce in Tana River and beyond. The institution strives to be a center of excellence in TVET within the arid and semi-arid lands (ASALs) region it serves.	Ministry of Education	["TVC", "College", "Technical", "Vocational"]	01986e2d-1ba3-7ba9-8054-0c158b31f73c	2025-10-06 14:51:29.591579	2025-08-03 04:25:06.724002	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	fayya-technical-and-vocational-college
Kajiado East Technical & Vocational College	Kajiado East Technical & Vocational College (KETVC) is a public TVET institution located in Mashuru, Kajiado County, Kenya. It offers diverse technical and vocational programs aimed at equipping students with practical skills for various industries, contributing to national development.	COLLEGE	KAJIADO EAST TVC	Kajiado County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/4350/	PUBLIC	Kajiado East Technical & Vocational College (KETVC) is a dynamic public TVET institution situated in Mashuru, Kajiado East Constituency, Kajiado County, Kenya. Established to address the growing demand for skilled manpower in the region and nationally, KETVC plays a crucial role in providing accessible and relevant technical and vocational training. The college is dedicated to offering a wide array of courses across various disciplines, designed to meet the needs of both students seeking employment and industries requiring competent professionals. Its curriculum is structured to provide hands-on experience and practical knowledge, preparing graduates for immediate entry into the workforce or for further education.\n\nKETVC operates under the Ministry of Education and is a registered institution under TVETA (Technical and Vocational Education and Training Authority). It is also listed among the institutions whose programs are accessible through the Kenya Universities and Colleges Central Placement Service (KUCCPS), facilitating student admissions from across the country. Located in a semi-arid region, the college not only serves the local community but also attracts students from beyond, contributing to the socio-economic development of Kajiado County. The institution is committed to fostering innovation, entrepreneurship, and community engagement through its training programs and activities, aiming to be a leading center for technical and vocational excellence in Kenya.	Ministry of Education	["TVC", "College", "Technical", "Vocational"]	01986e2f-04ed-7028-a27e-c318e0465c35	2025-10-06 14:51:29.591637	2025-08-03 04:27:11.98115	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	kajiado-east-technical-vocational-college
Karen Technical Training Institute For The Deaf	Karen Technical Training Institute For The Deaf is a unique public college in Karen, Nairobi, dedicated to providing technical and vocational training to young deaf individuals. It offers specialized programs equipping students with practical skills for employment and self-reliance.	COLLEGE	KAREN TTI	Nairobi County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/1440/	PUBLIC	Karen Technical Training Institute For The Deaf (KTTID) is a distinguished public technical training institution situated in the serene suburb of Karen, Nairobi. Established initially in 1990 by the Africa Inland Church (AIC) Kenya and later becoming a government institution in 1992, KTTID holds the unique mandate of providing specialized technical and vocational education and training (TVET) to deaf youth across Kenya. Its establishment was a significant step towards inclusivity in education, ensuring that deaf individuals have access to quality technical skills necessary for their integration into the workforce and society. The institute is located on Langata South Road, providing a conducive learning environment away from the city bustle.\n\nKTTID offers a diverse range of programs tailored to meet the needs and abilities of its deaf learners, delivered through accessible methods like Kenyan Sign Language. Courses span various technical fields including Masonry, Carpentry, Tailoring, Electrical Installation, ICT, Motor Vehicle Mechanics, Hairdressing and Beauty Therapy, and Sign Language Interpretation. The curriculum is designed not only to impart technical skills but also to foster entrepreneurship, communication, and life skills. As a public institution under the Ministry of Education, KTTID plays a crucial role in empowering the deaf community by equipping them with practical trades that enhance their employability and ability to contribute meaningfully to the economy. Its reputation is built on its specialized focus, dedicated staff, and successful graduates who have made strides in various sectors.	Ministry of Education	["TTI", "Institute", "Technical"]	01986e2f-3c96-7ca9-ac98-649e84ea95ed	2025-10-06 14:51:29.591647	2025-08-03 04:27:26.230876	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	karen-technical-training-institute-for-the-deaf
Aberdare Teachers Training College	Aberdare Teachers Training College, a public institution in Nyahururu, Nyandarua County, under the Ministry of Education, specializes in training primary school teachers. Committed to excellence in teacher education.	COLLEGE	ABERDARE TTC	Nyandarua County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/4480/	PUBLIC	Aberdare Teachers Training College is a public institution located in Nyahururu, within Nyandarua County, Kenya. It falls under the supervision of the Ministry of Education and is dedicated to training primary school teachers. The college plays a vital role in the Kenyan education system by equipping aspiring educators with the necessary skills and knowledge to effectively teach and nurture young learners.\n\nThe college provides a conducive learning environment with qualified trainers and resources to facilitate effective teaching and learning. Aberdare TTC is committed to producing highly competent teachers who can contribute significantly to the improvement of primary education standards in Kenya. The college offers a Primary Teacher Education (PTE) program.	Ministry of Education	["College", "TTC", "Teachers"]	01986e2a-b765-7c46-8534-57bf88334971	2025-10-06 14:51:29.591499	2025-08-03 04:22:29.989924	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	aberdare-teachers-training-college
Kenya Medical Training College - Eldoret Campus	Kenya Medical Training College, Eldoret Campus, is a public institution specializing in training mid-level health professionals. Located in Eldoret, Uasin Gishu County, it offers a range of diploma and certificate programs crucial for Kenya's healthcare sector.	COLLEGE	KMTC - ELDORET	Uasin Gishu County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/4755/	PUBLIC	The Kenya Medical Training College (KMTC) Eldoret Campus is a prominent constituent college of KMTC, a state corporation under the Ministry of Health in Kenya. Established as one of the many campuses spread across the nation, KMTC Eldoret plays a vital role in training qualified healthcare professionals to serve in various capacities within the Kenyan health system. Located in Eldoret, Uasin Gishu County, along the Eldoret-Kapsabet Road, the campus provides a conducive learning environment for students pursuing careers in diverse medical fields.\n\nKMTC Eldoret offers a wide array of programs at diploma and certificate levels, including but not limited to Nursing, Clinical Medicine, Medical Laboratory Sciences, Health Records and Information Technology, and Pharmacy. These programs are designed to equip students with the necessary theoretical knowledge and practical skills required for effective healthcare delivery. The campus attracts students from the surrounding region and beyond, contributing significantly to the availability of skilled medical personnel in the Rift Valley and Kenya as a whole. It maintains strong ties with local healthcare facilities, particularly the Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital (MTRH), providing students with essential clinical practice opportunities. The institution is recognized for its standardized curriculum and contributes significantly to Kenya's health outcomes by producing competent graduates.	Ministry of Health	["College", "Medical"]	01986e30-353d-75ae-ab27-089183347afc	2025-10-06 14:51:29.591679	2025-08-03 04:28:29.885554	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	kenya-medical-training-college-eldoret-campus
Kenya Medical Training College - Gatundu - Mutunguru Satellite Campus	Kenya Medical Training College - Gatundu - Mutunguru Satellite Campus is a public medical training institution located in Mutunguru, Gatundu South, Kiambu County. It is a satellite campus providing accessible healthcare training programs.	COLLEGE	KMTC - GATUNDU - MUTUNGURU SATELLITE	Kiambu County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/4775/	PUBLIC	The Kenya Medical Training College (KMTC) - Gatundu - Mutunguru Satellite Campus is one of the many constituent campuses operating under the umbrella of the national Kenya Medical Training College. Established to decentralize medical education and increase accessibility, this satellite campus serves the Mutunguru area within Gatundu South Constituency in Kiambu County. It plays a crucial role in training healthcare professionals at the certificate and diploma levels, contributing to the healthcare workforce in the region and nationally. As a public institution under the Ministry of Health, KMTC campuses adhere to standardized curricula and training quality, aiming to produce competent and ethical healthcare providers.\n\nThe establishment of satellite campuses like the one in Mutunguru reflects KMTC's strategic plan to expand its reach beyond major urban centers. By bringing training opportunities closer to rural and semi-urban populations, the Mutunguru campus enables local residents to pursue careers in healthcare without necessarily relocating far from home. While specific program offerings at satellite campuses can be tailored to regional needs or available facilities, they generally cover fundamental healthcare disciplines. The campus is integrated into the local community and healthcare infrastructure, potentially involving attachments or collaborations with nearby health facilities for practical training.	Ministry of Health	["College", "Medical"]	01986e30-460b-7969-918f-c30e4bea3a84	2025-10-06 14:51:29.591682	2025-08-03 04:28:34.18786	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	kenya-medical-training-college-gatundu-mutunguru-satellite-campus
Kenya Medical Training College - Teso Campus	Kenya Medical Training College (KMTC) - Teso Campus is a public institution located in Amagoro, Busia County. It is a constituent college of KMTC, dedicated to training healthcare professionals at certificate and diploma levels to serve the region and Kenya.	COLLEGE	KMTC - TESO	Busia County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/5095/	PUBLIC	Kenya Medical Training College (KMTC) is a state corporation under the Ministry of Health, mandated to train healthcare professionals in Kenya. Established in 1927, KMTC has grown into a major provider of health education with numerous campuses spread across the country. The establishment of campuses like KMTC Teso aims to decentralize training opportunities and bring medical education closer to various communities, addressing regional healthcare needs and promoting equitable access to training. The Teso campus is part of this broader initiative to increase the output of qualified health personnel in diverse fields, contributing significantly to the national healthcare workforce.\n\nLocated in Amagoro, Teso North Constituency, Busia County, KMTC Teso Campus serves students primarily from the western parts of Kenya and beyond. The campus offers a range of medical training programs at certificate and diploma levels, covering disciplines essential for the healthcare sector. While specific program offerings may vary over time, typical courses mirror those offered across the KMTC network, including disciplines like Nursing, Clinical Medicine, and Medical Laboratory Sciences. The campus adheres to the established curriculum and rigorous standards of the national KMTC institution, playing a crucial role in equipping students with the skills required to serve in hospitals and clinics, thereby supporting healthcare delivery in the region and the country.	Ministry of Health	["College", "Medical"]	01986e31-d340-70d7-8882-3149e7b1b90a	2025-10-06 14:51:29.591757	2025-08-03 04:30:15.872166	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	kenya-medical-training-college-teso-campus
