Technical University Of Mombasa Tvet Institute	The Technical University of Mombasa TVET Institute is a public technical and vocational training institution located in Mombasa County. Part of the Technical University of Mombasa, it offers practical-oriented Diploma and Certificate programs focusing on various technical fields to equip students with industry-relevant skills for the job market.	COLLEGE	TUM TVET	Mombasa County	https://students.kuccps.net/institutions/5395/	PUBLIC	The Technical University of Mombasa TVET Institute operates as a key constituent part of the Technical University of Mombasa (TUM), a prominent public university located in the coastal city of Mombasa, Kenya. TUM itself evolved from the former Mombasa Polytechnic, which was established in 1948. This historical lineage imbues the TVET institute with a long-standing tradition of technical and vocational education. Situated within the vibrant and strategically important Mombasa County, the institute benefits from the region's coastal economy and its position as a major transport and industrial hub.\n\nThe TVET Institute is dedicated to offering demand-driven technical and vocational education and training programs, primarily at Diploma and Certificate levels, as listed through admissions bodies like KUCCPS. Its curriculum focuses on providing students with practical skills and theoretical knowledge essential for direct entry into various industries. As a public institution under the University TVET category, it plays a crucial role in national development by producing a skilled workforce ready to contribute to sectors such as engineering, business, hospitality, and applied sciences, thereby enhancing Kenya's technical capacity and supporting economic growth.	University TVET	["University", "Technical", "Institute", "TVET"]	01986e39-d0a6-75a5-9a74-39a1b7c1e1ee	2025-10-06 14:51:29.592018	2025-08-03 04:38:59.494447	\N	01986e2a-aa36-7386-9bdf-ab2aff6ac71e	technical-university-of-mombasa-tvet-institute
